FATAL ILLNESS - PAKISTAN: (SINDH) CHILDREN, CONFLICTING DIAGNOSES, REQUEST FOR INFORMATION
******************************************************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

[1]
Date: Mon 19 Nov 2012
Source: The Nation [edited]
http://www.nation.com.pk/pakistan-news-newspaper-daily-english-online/national/19-Nov-2012/three-children-die-of-smallpox-in-khairpur


Three children died of smallpox in [Thari Mirwah taluka (sub-district)] in Khairpur district. 3 children [names withheld - Mod.CP] died at village Ajeeb Dasti near Thari Mirwah. According to villagers, a total of 7 children died during the last 48 hours in different villages, but the health department or district administration are still unaware in this regard. They said due to poor services of the health department, medicines are stolen from health centres while the district administration is also not paying attention in this regard.

They have demanded dispatch of doctor teams to their areas as several people including children are suffering from smallpox disease and the people are scared of the rising death toll.

[Almost identical reports report have appeared in the Frontier Post http://www.thefrontierpost.com/article/192722/, and the Lahore Tines http://www.promedmail.org/direct.php?id=20020612.4479.]

